<subSubSection lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,1785,2028]" lastBlockId="54.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1785,1811]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Length 7.0 mm. Postocular plate with golden pollinosity. Ocellar bristles weakly developed. Thorax and abdomen with pale golden pollinosity. Two well-differentiated posterior and 2 smaller anterior postsutural dorsocentrals. Apical scutellar bristles absent. Legs blackish. T3 with 1 pair of lateral marginal bristles. Cercus sinuous in lateral view, with normal (i.e., as broad as median area), obliquely cut apex. Cercus with bristles ventrally only in distal third. Cerci with distal third as broad as middle part in posterior view; parallel and with a distinct constriction mid length. Pregonite with expanded base, gradually narrowing to apex; unicolorous. Postgonite with expanded base and sudden narrowing at apex; unicolorous. Distiphallus with smooth ventroapical margin, conical apex and straight dorsal outline. Vesica symmetrical, with angular median projection of main branch; distal lobes well developed, with filaments, tapering, sclerotized, with spines only along ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</emphasis>
The single specimen examined presents a damaged abdomen, partially lacking T4 and entirely lacking T5 and ST5. Its terminalia are preserved in glycerin in a microtube. The original description mentions that T5 is yellow and that T4 lacks median marginal bristles, but there are no remarks regarding ST5 (
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S." box="[1226,1375,294,321]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="485 - 489" refId="ref110669" refString="Lopes, H. S. (1975 e) On some new species of Sarcophagidae from Costa Rica (Diptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 35 (3), 485 - 489." type="journal article" year="1975">Lopes 1975e</bibRefCitation>
). The cercus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" box="[258,387,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floricola">
<emphasis box="[258,387,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">O. floricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[402,496,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 117–122" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1510,1534]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,591,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-162@54.[151,1435,561,1486]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 117–122. Oxysarcodexia spp., males. 117–119. Oxysarcodexia flavipes Lopes &amp; Tibana (Argentina, MACN). 117. Habitus, lateral view. 118. Terminalia, lateral view. 119. Terminalia, posterior view. 120–122. Oxysarcodexia floricola Lopes (Brazil, Santa Catarina, Seara, Nova Teutonia, MNRJ). 120. Habitus, lateral view. 121. Terminalia, lateral view. 122. Terminalia, posterior view. Figs 117–119 by P.R. Mulieri (MACN)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405637/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 122</figureCitation>
) resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Souza &amp; Buenaventura" authorityYear="2016" box="[705,861,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laclaricola">
<emphasis box="[705,861,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">O. laclaricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
