<figureCitation box="[875,973,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 157–165" captionStartId="68.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[189,1405,303,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-46@68.[151,1435,273,1785]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURES 157–165. Oxysarcodexia spp., males. 157–159. Oxysarcodexia jamesi Dodge (Costa Rica, Guanacaste Province, MNRJ). 157. Habitus, lateral view. 158. Terminalia, lateral view. 159. Terminalia, posterior view. 160–162. Oxysarcodexia laclaricola Souza &amp; Buenaventura, holotype (Colombia, Antioquia, Caldas, La Clara, CE-TdeA). 160. Habitus, lateral view. 161. Terminalia, lateral view. 162. Terminalia, posterior view. 163–165. Oxysarcodexia liliarum Souza &amp; Buenaventura, holotype (Colombia, Antioquia, Caldas, La Clara, CE-TdeA). 163. Habitus, lateral view. 164. Terminalia, lateral view. 165. Terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405651/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 162</figureCitation>
